<subSubSection id="E482A7B635619A3CFF31C4DFA961F855" pageId="15" pageNumber="385" type="description">
<paragraph id="AC27F43D35619A3CFF31C4DFA8C7F88F" blockId="15.[159,772,1207,2018]" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">
Twenty-five individuals were recorded from 10 sites in southern and northern 
<collectingCountry id="D48FB4AD35619A3CFDF6C4B1AA8CFB44" box="[514,672,1241,1267]" name="Mozambique" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
, making it the second most widespread species encountered during this study. The species has probably been overlooked in central 
<collectingCountry id="D48FB4AD35619A3CFE54C528AA17FAED" box="[416,571,1344,1370]" name="Mozambique" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
since it has been recorded there in the past (
<bibRefCitation id="C80989CC35619A3CFDF7C50AA906FA29" author="SMITHERS, R. H. N. &amp; J. L. P. LOBAO TELLO" pageId="15" pageNumber="385" pagination="1 - 184" refId="ref14678" refString="SMITHERS, R. H. N., and J. L. P. LOBAO TELLO. 1976. Check list and atlas of the mammals of Mozambique. Museum Memoir, The Trustees of the National Museums and Monuments of Rhodesia, 8: 1 - 184." type="journal article" year="1976">Smithers and Lobão Tello, 1976</bibRefCitation>
). Toward absolving the confusion associated with the status of this taxon, the smallest yellow-bellied species of 
<taxonomicName id="6B988FBE35619A3CFE2AC5A0AA4BFA55" box="[478,615,1480,1506]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9EEC282F35619A3CFE2AC5A0AA4BFA55" box="[478,615,1480,1506]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">Scotophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in Southern Africa were assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="6B988FBE35619A3CFE2DC583AA65F9B2" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[473,585,1515,1541]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis id="9EEC282F35619A3CFE2DC583AA65F9B2" box="[473,585,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">S. viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="C80989CC35619A3CFD70C583A912F990" author="MONADJEM, A. &amp; P. J. TAYLOR &amp; F. P. D. COTTERILL &amp; M. C. SCHOEMAN" pageId="15" pageNumber="385" refId="ref14234" refString="MONADJEM, A., P. J. TAYLOR, F. P. D. COTTERILL, and M. C. SCHOEMAN. 2010. Bats of Southern and Central Africa: a biogeographic and taxonomic synthesis. University of the Witwatersrand, Johannesburg, 596 pp." type="book" year="2010">
Monadjem 
<emphasis id="9EEC282F35619A3CFF6BC665A8CCF990" box="[159,224,1549,1575]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
(2010)
</bibRefCitation>
, distinct from the similar sized, but cream-bellied 
<taxonomicName id="6B988FBE35619A3CFEB8C647A9D4F9FE" baseAuthorityName="Cretzschmar" baseAuthorityYear="1826" box="[332,504,1583,1609]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucogaster">
<emphasis id="9EEC282F35619A3CFEB8C647A9D4F9FE" box="[332,504,1583,1609]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">S. leucogaster</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The recent paper by 
<bibRefCitation id="C80989CC35619A3CFF6BC639A9D2F9DC" author="JACOBS, D. S. &amp; R. M. R. BARCLAY" box="[159,510,1617,1643]" pageId="15" pageNumber="385" pagination="879 - 887" refId="ref13779" refString="JACOBS, D. S., and R. M. R. BARCLAY. 2009. Niche differentiation in two sympatric sibling bat species Scotophilus dinganii and Scotophilus mhlanganii. Journal of Mammalogy, 90: 879 - 887." type="journal article" year="2009">Jacobs and Barclay (2009)</bibRefCitation>
, assigned the name 
<emphasis id="9EEC282F35619A3CFF6BC61BA899F93A" box="[159,181,1651,1677]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">S.</emphasis>
‘ 
<emphasis id="9EEC282F35619A3CFF25C61BA974F93A" box="[209,344,1651,1677]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">mhlanganii</emphasis>
’ for their studied population of this small, yellow-bellied 
<taxonomicName id="6B988FBE35619A3CFE0CC6FDAAA9F918" box="[504,645,1685,1711]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="385" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9EEC282F35619A3CFE0CC6FDAAA9F918" box="[504,645,1685,1711]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">Scotophilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but this most unfortunate introduction of a nomen nudum into an already confusing taxonomy has created more problems than it solves (
<bibRefCitation id="C80989CC35619A3CFDDDC694A8F3F88F" author="MONADJEM, A. &amp; P. J. TAYLOR &amp; F. P. D. COTTERILL &amp; M. C. SCHOEMAN" pageId="15" pageNumber="385" refId="ref14234" refString="MONADJEM, A., P. J. TAYLOR, F. P. D. COTTERILL, and M. C. SCHOEMAN. 2010. Bats of Southern and Central Africa: a biogeographic and taxonomic synthesis. University of the Witwatersrand, Johannesburg, 596 pp." type="book" year="2010">
Monadjem 
<emphasis id="9EEC282F35619A3CFD4DC694AAD0F8A1" box="[697,764,1788,1814]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">et al.</emphasis>
, 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AC27F43D35619A3CFF31C728A961F855" blockId="15.[159,772,1207,2018]" pageId="15" pageNumber="385">Field measurements: FA (adult male) 46.4 ± 1.22 (44.1–48.2, 17); Bm (adult male) 19.2 ± 2.90 (16.0– 24.5, 16); FA (adult female) 47.7 ± 2.06 (45.4–51.7, 8); Bm (adult female) 26.1 ± 7.06 (17.0–33.0, 6).</paragraph>
